cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper investigates the simultaneous wireless power and information transfer (SWIPT) for network-coded two-way relay transmission from an information theoretical viewpoint. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a time switching (TS) relay receiver architecture for two-way relaying and formulates an optimization problem under total power constraint to explore the system throughput limit with data rate fairness. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design of a protocol for two-way relaying and optimization of system throughput, which can be considered as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed protocol in terms of data rate fairness, which is a key factor in multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper presents an efficient algorithm to solve the optimization problem formulated for the proposed protocol, which can be considered as a computational engineering problem.
